{"lemma": "ضَيْعَةٌ", "slug": "ضَيْعَةٌ", "root": "ض.#.ع", "root_slug": "ض-_-ع", "root_link": "/words/roots/ض-_-ع", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n26194"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "pasture", "fa": "چراگاه", "ur": "چروا", "tr": "çayır", "id": "padang rumput", "bn": "চারণভূমি", "es": "prado", "fr": "pâturage", "de": "Weide", "ru": "пастбище", "zh": "牧场"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "pasture, meadowland, grazing ground"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "estate, property, domain"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "village, hamlet"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Borrowed from Ge'ez ፂኦት (ṣ́iʾot, “low grounds, pasture”) according to Nöldeke."}, "ipa": ["/dˤaj.ʕa/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n26194", "headword_ar": "ضَيْعَةٌ", "root": "DyE", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "an inf. n. of 1. (S, &c.) ―         -b2-  See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DayaAEN", "text_ar": "ضَيَاعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", below, last sentence but one. ―         -b3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A single case,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "occasion, of perishing, coming to nought, passing away,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "becoming lost;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of being left, left"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "let alone,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "neglected."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tarakotuhu", "text_ar": "تَرَكْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biDayoEapK", "text_ar": "بِضَيْعَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I left him unsought-after,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "unminded,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "unmissed."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA. [See also a similar phrase voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DayaAEN", "text_ar": "ضَيَاعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".])       -A2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaqaArN", "text_ar": "عَقَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An estate consisting of land,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of land and a house,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a house"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "land yielding a revenue,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a house and palm-trees,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S, O, Msb, K;) and [particularly]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "land yielding a revenue;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) or with the people of the towns and villages and cultivated lands it signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "property,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a man,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "consisting of palm-trees and grape-vines and land:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but the Arabs [of the desert] know not the word in this sense: (Az, TA:) IF says, I do not reckon the application of this word as a name for the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaqaAr", "text_ar": "عَقَار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to be of the original language, but think it to be an innovation in speech; and I have heard it said that this is termed a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DyEp", "text_ar": "ضيعة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because, when frequent attention to it is neglected, it perishes; and if it be so, this is an evidence of what we have said, that it is of the innovated speech: (O, TA:) the dim. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DuyayoEapN", "text_ar": "ضُيَيْعَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for which one should not say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DuwayoEapN", "text_ar": "ضُوَيْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, O, K:) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DiyaAEN", "text_ar": "ضِيَاعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DiyaEN", "text_ar": "ضِيَعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, Msb, K,) as though the latter were a contraction of the former, (Msb,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DayoEaAtN", "text_ar": "ضَيْعَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) accord. to Lth, the first of these pls. signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "places of alighting"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abode"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "settlement;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "which are thus called because, when the paying frequent attention to them, or taking good care of them, and the keeping them, or putting them, in a good state, or state of repair, is neglected, they come to nought: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DayoEaAtN", "text_ar": "ضَيْعَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "occurs in a trad. as meaning the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "means of subsistence."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) And, (T, O, Msb, K,) as used by the Arabs [of the desert], who know not the word in any other sense than this, (T, O,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A craft,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "handicraft, by which one gains his subsistence; a mode,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "manner, of gain;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1813}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "habitual work"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "occupation"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a man; (T, O, Msb, K) as the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sewing of skins"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "boots"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "twisting of ropes;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weaving,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "plaiting, of palm-leaves;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "culture of palm-trees"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eamalu Aln~axoli", "text_ar": "عَمَلُ النَّخْلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "); and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pasturing of camels;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like thereof;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, O;) including the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sowing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tilling, of land:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DayoEap", "text_ar": "ضَيْعَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the Arabs was the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "management,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tending, of camels"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of sheep and goats:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the term includes a man's"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "craft,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "handicraft,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "means of gain:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Sh, O:) and his"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "traffic:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Sh, O, K:) one says to a man,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qumo A_ilaY DayoEatika", "text_ar": "قُمْ اـِلَى ضَيْعَتِكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Arise to thy craft,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]: (Sh, O:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~u rajulK", "text_ar": "كُلُّ رَجُلٍ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waDayoEatahu", "text_ar": "وَضَيْعَتَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Every man"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "should occupy himself"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with his"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "proper"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "craft,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.] (Msb.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afo$aY A@ll~`hu", "text_ar": "اَفْشَى ا@للّٰهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DayoEatahu", "text_ar": "ضَيْعَتَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", occurring in a trad., means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "God made"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may God make, his means of subsistence to be abundant."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) And one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fa$ato DayoEatuhu", "text_ar": "فَشَتْ ضَيْعَتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [or, more commonly,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fa$ato Ealayohi DayoEatuhu", "text_ar": "فَشَتْ عَلَيْهِ ضَيْعَتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as in the TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "f$w", "text_ar": "فشو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", &c.,] which is said to mean"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His property was,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became, large,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abundant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wide-spread,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so that he was unable to collect it together:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [hence]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his means of attaining his object"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his affairs"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(as in the TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "f$w", "text_ar": "فشو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became disordered so that he knew not with which of them to begin:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he took to doing an affair that did not concern him:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA, and Ham p. 33:) it is nearly like the saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ait~asaEa Alxaroqu", "text_ar": "اِتَّسَعَ الخَرْقُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY Alr~aAqiEi", "text_ar": "عَلَى الرَّاقِعِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[expl. in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xrq", "text_ar": "خرق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Ham ibid.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~iY laA^araY DayoEapF laA yuSoliHuhaA A_il~aA DajoEapN", "text_ar": "اـِنِّى لَاَرَى ضَيْعَةً لَا يُصْلِحُهَا اـِلَّا ضَجْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily I see property that nothing but a sleep will restore to a right state"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] a prov.; said by a pastor whose camels had dispersed themselves, and who, desiring to collect them together, and being unable to do so, sought aid of sleep. (O.)"}], "source_refs": ["Az", "TA", "O", "S", "K", "Msb", "T", "Sh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}